  "prompt": "How do I write good essays in English?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for writing good essays in English:\n\n1. Understand the assignment\n- Read the prompt carefully\n- Note key requirements and guidelines\n\n2. Plan and outline\n- Brainstorm ideas\n- Create a clear structure\n- Develop a thesis statement\n\n3. Research thoroughly\n- Use credible sources\n- Take good notes\n- Keep track of references\n\n4. Write a strong introduction\n- Start with an engaging hook\n- Provide background context\n- State your thesis clearly\n\n5. Develop clear body paragraphs\n- Each paragraph should have a main idea\n- Use evidence and examples\n- Explain how evidence supports your thesis\n- Use transitions between paragraphs\n\n6. Craft a compelling conclusion\n- Restate your thesis\n- Summarize main points\n- Provide final insights\n\n7. Improve writing style\n- Use varied sentence structures\n- Choose precise vocabulary\n- Avoid passive voice\n- Be concise\n\n8. Edit and proofread\n- Check grammar and spelling\n- Ensure logical flow\n- Read your essay out loud\n- Get feedback from others\n\n9. Practice regularly\n- Read academic writing\n- Write frequently\n- Learn from feedback\n\n10. Follow proper citation format\n- Use MLA, APA, or Chicago style as required",
